column5: just thought i'd share some pics of fish i've iced this ice fishing season
Nice take Dude !!!! Looks like yer gonna miss da hice !!!!!!!!!!!
looks like you had a blast this season... awesome pics. thnx for sharin
Nice gators, and some tasty pannies!  Always good eatin' during the hardwater season.
Nice haul for sure, I just can`t get motivated to do the icefishing thing anymore probably has something to do with temperature!!!
What is that first fish? A rainbow? It's really long and thin Nice season Miller... thosepike are beauties.

first picture and third picture are the same fish. when i pulled it out i thought rainbow at first then a guy near by told me he thought it was a coho. the top of the back including fins and tail were black. i am no species expert so its up in the air for me lol
Nice fish you got this season Miller.
def sum sort of salmon specie, atlantic? i think i see sum red dots and def a forked tail.. nice fish dude, i to hit up the local marinas around here for pike and what ever else hits!
Sounds like you had a good season    Nicely done miller

yeah i was thinking it was a salmon species but who knows.  local marinas can have some great fishing. on lake o you never know what you'll hook into. one morning i had 3 rainbows break me off at the hole(6") and the next day i landed two pike
mmmmm crappie. Looks like a few good trips were had this season.  Art
